Suppress the top-screen SDL cursor unless the companion "Game cursor" option is on.

The investigation into the lingering gamepad cursor during split-conversation
mode found that the cursor reappears through THREE paths that the earlier
companion-hideui-gamepad-cursor.patch does not cover:
  1. Left thumbstick  - ControllerManager::update() -> setCursorActive(true)
  2. Right thumbstick  - same update() via the mouse-wheel term
  3. Touch-to-mouse    - MouseManager::mouseMoved() -> setCursorActive(true)
                         (also re-arms mGamepadGuiCursorEnabled, undoing the patch)
All three ultimately show the SDL hardware cursor through the one per-frame call
    InputManager::update -> setMouseVisible(getCursorVisible())
so gating THAT single choke point catches all three at once, regardless of the
mCursorActive/mCursorVisible flags the individual paths flip.

The gate reads companionCursorEnabled() (androidmain.cpp), fed from Kotlin's
UiPreferences "gameCursor" option via setCompanionCursorEnabled(); default false =
cursor suppressed. A second, belt-and-suspenders gate is added to the menu-cursor
path in WindowManager::updateVisible() (setCursorVisible(!gameMode)) that re-enables
the cursor in GUI modes including GM_Dialogue, so it too respects the option.

Both edits are #ifdef __ANDROID__ so desktop behavior is unchanged.

diff --git a/apps/openmw/mwinput/inputmanagerimp.cpp b/apps/openmw/mwinput/inputmanagerimp.cpp
--- a/apps/openmw/mwinput/inputmanagerimp.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwinput/inputmanagerimp.cpp
@@ -23,5 +23,12 @@
 #include "sensormanager.hpp"
 
+#ifdef __ANDROID__
+// COMPANION: defined in androidmain.cpp. Returns false while the companion "Game
+// cursor" option is off, so the top-screen SDL cursor is suppressed for touch and
+// both thumbsticks at once (all funnel through the per-frame setMouseVisible below).
+extern "C" bool companionCursorEnabled();
+#endif
+
 namespace MWInput
 {
     InputManager::InputManager(SDL_Window* window, osg::ref_ptr<osgViewer::Viewer> viewer,
@@ -58,6 +58,14 @@
     void InputManager::update(float dt, bool disableControls, bool disableEvents)
     {
         mControlsDisabled = disableControls;
 
-        mInputWrapper->setMouseVisible(MWBase::Environment::get().getWindowManager()->getCursorVisible());
+        bool companionCursorVisible = MWBase::Environment::get().getWindowManager()->getCursorVisible();
+#ifdef __ANDROID__
+        // COMPANION: keep the top-screen SDL cursor hidden while the "Game cursor"
+        // option is off. This single per-frame choke point catches left stick, right
+        // stick and touch-to-mouse at once, regardless of mCursorActive/mCursorVisible.
+        if (!companionCursorEnabled())
+            companionCursorVisible = false;
+#endif
+        mInputWrapper->setMouseVisible(companionCursorVisible);
         mInputWrapper->capture(disableEvents);
